data.output: I had to put some diesel into my car as I was going on a long trip and needed to make sure that I was able to get there as quickly as possible without refuelling.  I went to the petrol station to get the diesel but there was a commotion happening at the pump that was free.  A crowd of people were gathered around all looking down towards the ground.  I got out of my car to see what was happening and what did I see, but a tiny kitten!!! Ginger and white and crying so loudly for all the size of it!! It was so cute but goodness, where did it come from?  .

My mother said she never gets any post anymore, that everything is by email or phone call!! So I decided to give her a surprise and write her a little letter.  I could send it on the way home from work and she would get it hopefully in a few days.  I got out my notecards and sent a little hello from me and quickly put it in the envelope.  Oh no, I needed a stamp!!

Our local church had received a letter from the council to let them know that the organ that is played regularly at the church services needed to comply with regulation for health and safety reasons.  The minister asked me if I knew anyone who could possibly help with this as he didn't know the first thing about it!! I asked my friend who worked at the Empire theatre in the town if she knew anyone who perhaps would be able to do it.  Luckily we found someone!!!  Thank goodness!!!

It was a day full of despair and gloom, I felt so down thinking about the payment that was missing from my bank account.  It was causing so much bother at home and I just didn't know what to do about it.  Did I imagine it? Did it really exist? Did someone hack into my account?
